OpenSource Discover (“we”) operates the OpenSource Discover mobile application. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our App.

1. Information We Collect
   OpenSource Discover is a repository discovery application that helps users explore publicly available open-source projects.

We do not collect any personally identifiable information such as name, address, phone number, or payment details.

The App may collect non-personal information automatically, including:
Device type
Operating system version
App usage statistics (such as screens visited and time spent)
Crash reports and performance data

This information is used only to improve app performance and user experience.

3. Third-Party Services
   OpenSource Discover may use third-party services such as analytics and advertising tools to help us understand how the App is used and to support app functionality. These services may collect information in accordance with their own privacy policies.

Examples of third-party services:
Google Analytics for Firebase (if applicable)
Firebase Crashlytics
Google AdMob (if ads are enabled)

We do not control how third-party services handle data.

5. Repository Information
   The App displays publicly available open-source repository information obtained from publicly accessible sources and APIs.

OpenSource Discover acts only as an independent discovery tool and does not host or modify repository content.

The App is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or officially connected with any repository hosting platform or organization.

7. Children’s Privacy
   OpenSource Discover is intended for a general audience and may be used by students and developers.

We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13.

If you believe that a child has provided personal information, please contact us and we will remove it immediately.

9. Data Security
   We value your trust and strive to use reasonable security measures to protect information from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure.

10. Changes to This Privacy Policy
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and the updated date will be revised above.

11. Contact Us
    If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
    Email: [codinglance@gmail.com](mailto:codinglance@gmail.com)
